cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for interpreting the activity of neurons in a deep neural network, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method involves isolating subnetworks and examining patterns in input instances, which is also relevant to neural network architecture and optimization (cs.NE). The authors also mention the use of their method in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), indicating potential applications in these subfields.
